description:
Wildlife Instincts - Episode 6: Whitespotted Bamboo Shark | Wildlife Documentary

Watch 'Wildlife Instincts - Episode 7' here: https://youtu.be/9pxWMzI-dV0

Every year a bay in Japan becomes a hive of white-spotted bamboo shark activity.

The black striped and white spotted sharks enjoy life on the seabed. For most of the year they inhabit deep waters; however, every summer the distinctive sharks congregate in the bay.
Little is known about the elusive sharks movements outside of the bay, but in the shallow waters they mate and give birth to the next generation. Like many shark species, white-spotted bamboo sharks are oviparous. The females are ingenious egg layers and work relentlessly to find the perfect spawning grounds. Every egg is brilliantly camouflaged - but there are many would be egg thieves lurking in the bays tranquil waters....
